Subject: LM Studio Corpus Prompt Outside Preservation 011

Description: Diversified LM Studio worker prompt packet for outside preservation.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop

& [LMStudioCorpusPrompt:outside_preservation_011] is a non-mutating SOP worker prompt packet
  + [task_family] is outside_preservation
  + [prompt_boundary] is prompt-only, no tools, no file reads, no repo mutation, no hidden-state claims
  + [expected_output] is exactly one raw SOP node named InferenceJobResult with seven property lines and no Markdown
  + [validation_required_fields] is focus, inside, boundary, outside, inference, caution, next_step
  + [validation_required_terms] is outside, uncertainty, unsupported, boundary
  + [validation_forbidden_terms] is direct trust, hidden state access, broad competence, file mutation
  + [prompt_text] is:
    You are performing a no-tools SOP inference job from this prompt only.
    Do not call tools, inspect files, mutate state, or claim repo authority.
    Codex owns launch, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes.

    SOP primer:
    & [Name] is a subject declaration.
    + [field] is a property or inferred field.
    (attention) :inside: /boundary/ |outside| means inside belongs in focus, boundary separates identity, and outside is uncertainty or out-of-scope material.

    Task family:
    outside_preservation tests whether unsupported claims, unknowns, risks, and foreign context stay in outside while the local task is still answered.

    Subject to answer:
    "A worker claims a local model is generally reliable after two successful isolated runs on one prompt family."

    Return exactly these eight raw SOP lines and no extra text:
    & [InferenceJobResult] is outside preservation proposal
      + [focus] is ...
      + [inside] is ...
      + [boundary] is ...
      + [outside] is ...
      + [inference] is ...
      + [caution] is ...
      + [next_step] is ...

    Final check before answering:
    Line 1 must start with &.
    Lines 2 through 8 must use exactly this operator form: two spaces, +, space, [field], space, is, space, value.
    Do not replace is with verbs such as includes, separates, reminds, lists, or contains.
    Replace every ... placeholder with specific content; do not output ellipses or placeholder text.
    Use ASCII only; avoid curly quotes, nonbreaking hyphens, and special punctuation.
    Include the literal terms outside, uncertainty, unsupported, and boundary at least once.
    Do not claim direct trust, hidden state access, broad competence, or file mutation.
